In the current popup we are updating the domain instance value of a column in the list view from where this popup is being opened. The domain instance values that a list view column can take are MET, NOT MET and NOT KNOWN. But popup takes only MET and NOT MET. So when we are overriding the  NOT KNOWN value in the list view to either MET or NOT MET, framework throws a information telling given as below

&quot;The currently saved value for the eligibilityResultType drop down, Not Known, is not a member of the configured subset of values for that drop down and has been removed. Clicking OK will overwrite this value with the selected value in the drop down&quot;. 

This is happening because FDP framework is handling the updation of front end entered values to entity.If we use enum tag to display the dropdown, we have to directly bind the entity like
&lt;fineos:enum id=&quot;eligibilityResultType&quot; createLabel=&quot;true&quot;
				value=&quot;#{eligibilityResultOverridePopupWidget.eligibilityResult.eligibilityResultType}&quot;

 So as a work around for preventing the info message from popping up, we are using dropdown tag to display the dropdown and collect the value entered in the dropdown on the click of ok button and explicitly updating the entity class with the value selected in the dropdown

